TBH this is one mistake I can (and have to) live with: I live in Milan and am very often in Rome. I find the aesthetic of the white stone beautiful, while painted tin-soldier-like statues and monuments scattered around our cities would be carnivalesque and feel like a tacky Madame Tussauds.
I understand this is contrary to the principles of conservation, but I'm very happy it turned out like this.
